{"build_type":"library","description":"List an ALREADY-OPEN directory fd's entries as a document sequence of {name,type} entries sorted by name. Does not open or close the fd (caller owns it) — the dirfd-relative analog of list_directory_entries_with_type. Drains the directory completely via read_directory_into_array_via_getdents (getdents looped, no truncation) into the shared 1 MiB g_dirent_buffer (allocated once, reused, so memory is one buffer regardless of how many directories a walk visits; entry names are copied out during parsing so reuse is safe), then sorts via build_sorted_entry_copies. Reuses allocate_bytes_from_mmap_arena, begin_empty_sequence_document_value, read_directory_into_array_via_getdents, build_sorted_entry_copies.","module_name":"enumerate-entries-inside-opened-directory-stream","package_name":"enumerate-entries-inside-opened-directory-stream","module_globals":[{"global_name":"g_dirent_buffer","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"}],"function_definitions":{"enumerate-entries-inside-opened-directory-stream":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"fd","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"bufsize","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1048576},{"instruction_type":"global_read","dest":"buf","name":"g_dirent_buffer"},{"instruction_type":"conditional_branch","condition_type":"numeric_compare","operator":"==","lhs":{"value":"buf"},"rhs":{"value":"zero"},"branch_on_success":[{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"allocate-character-buffer-inside-memory-arena","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"bufsize"}],"result_assignment_variable":"buf","result_type":"i64"},{"instruction_type":"global_write","name":"g_dirent_buffer","value":"buf"}],"branch_on_failu